DOC.brief_summary: This study will evaluate the safety and efficacy of botulinum toxin Type A compared to placebo for the treatment of Crow's Feet Lines (Lateral Canthal Rhytides).
DOC.brief_title: Safety and Efficacy Study of Botulinum Toxin Type A for the Treatment of Crow's Feet Lines
DOC.criteria: Moderate to severe Crow's Feet Lines Have adequate vision without the use of eyeglasses to assess facial wrinkles in a mirror (contact lenses OK) Current or previous botulinum toxin treatment of any serotype Facial laser or light treatment, microdermabrasion or superficial peels within 3 months Oral retinoid therapy within 1 year Prior facial cosmetic surgery (eg, periorbital surgery, facial lift, brow lift, eye lift, or eyebrow surgery) Diagnosis of myasthenia gravis, EatonLambert syndrome, amyotrophic lateral sclerosis
